channel.title: Removing a google search result?
channel.description:
Whats up! Been a while since ive been on mopar :-)
Anyways,
When I type my name into google some search results come up I dont really like.. The search result has the title 'Porn bots' and some reply on that topic from me (From his site) (Its cached, I deleted the comment a looooooooong ago).
Would anyone know if there would be a way to remove the search result?
Thanks!

item.title: Removing a google search result?
item.dc:creator: @SilentCJ SilentCJ
item.description:
@SilentCJ wrote:

[quote=“youridudock, post:7, topic:464059”][quote author=SilentCJ link=topic=567840.msg4125220#msg4125220 date=1350315864]
Hah, there was plenty from here that had my real name in, but I just deleted them all, they disappear from search engines within a couple of days.
[/quote]

Did you delete them by your self? The comment is cached into the site :/[/quote]
Yep, there were a few posts where I’d given away where I live and my facebook and stuff, all of which were very near top when you search my irl name. I deleted them myself and within a few days they were gone.

Also did an image search for my name the other day, didn’t realise how many pictures (I wouldn’t want to be seen by businesses etc) of me there were as well.

Read full topic
